```

 **Expected behavior**
Webhook to startup correctly and certs created

 **To Reproduce**
1. Install Knative Eventing and Serving
2. Install Eventing RabbitMQ extension: https://knative.dev/docs/eventing/brokers/broker-types/rabbitmq-broker/
3. Uninstall the Eventing RabbitMQ resources.
4. Install again the Eventing RabbitMQ extension: https://knative.dev/docs/eventing/brokers/broker-types/rabbitmq-broker/

 **Knative release version**

v1.10.0

 **Additional context**
A similar issue was found in the Kafka webhook. https://github.com/knative/eventing-contrib/issues/1554

The workaround is to pass the below arg to `rabbitmq-broker-webhook` container.

```yaml
      containers:
        - name: rabbitmq-broker-webhook
          # Workaround to make broker webhook work. In case of deletion and recreation of resources in cluster secrets are not repopulated with the certificates
          args:
            - "--disable-ha"
```
